               <floruit notBefore="1300" notAfter="1450">
                  <persName ref="PRS10733ZirGan">Zir Gānelā</persName> 
                  is the name of the patroness of the de luxe illuminated manuscript of the <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1560Gospel">Four Gospels</ref>
                  which was commissioned for an unnamed monastery where <persName ref="PRS10733ZirGan">Zir Gānelā</persName> was abbess. 
                  <persName ref="PRS10733ZirGan">Zir Gānelā</persName> was a member of the royal family who rejected the fleeting world and became a nun. 
                  She entered the monastic life at the middle age, as she had two sons and two daughters. </floruit>
            
               
               
